
[1]scale-stone

   SCA'LE-STONE, n. A rare mineral, called also tafelspath and tabular
   spar, occurring in masses composed of thin lamins collected into large
   prismatic concretions or hexahedral prisms. It color is grayish or
   pearly white, tinged with green, yellow or red.
